channel.title: Sven coop run through this weekend?
channel.description:
This was actually an idea brought up by CornetTheory (Mike Hillard) in the BM steam chat. I thought he was gonna make a thread or something, but I guess not. It was a suggestion that before BM releases (probably gonna have to be this weekend) we'd play through Half life 1 via sven coop. I thought this would be pretty fun.
There's been no talk of times or servers yet, so [url='https://www.svencoop.com/mirrors.php']I'll just link to sven 4.6[/url] (the version most people have) and hope for the best. ____________________ [FONT='Arial Black'][COLOR='Red'][b][url='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3AQagqs9HVM&feature=player_detailpage#t=31s']update!!![/url][/b][/FONT][/SIZE] [FONT='Impact'][COLOR='DarkOrange']Nuclear Dan is hosting. We do this 1:00 PM US eastern time.[/SIZE][/FONT]
[FONT='Arial Black'][COLOR='Red'][b][url='https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3AQagqs9HVM&feature=player_detailpage#t=31s']update!!![/url][/b][/FONT][/SIZE]
[FONT='Impact'][COLOR='DarkOrange']Today is the day this shit goes down. join the BM chat and hopefully Dan will be there and will be able to tell you the actual IP. Player cap is 16, so get in fast.[/SIZE][/FONT]

item.dc:creator: Jethrosoup
item.description:
First video is up. It doesn’t show Half-Life yet, it’s the screwing around we did leading up to it, but it establishes the character of mouse which is necessary for understanding the complexities of the later player relationships.

I’m really sorry about how loud my voice is compared to the rest of the sound. Fraps recorded it at too high of a level.

The other 4-6 hours of it will be processed and uploaded tomorrow.
